STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Donald WASHINGTON, Appellant. No. ED 106217 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: June 11, 2019 FOR APPELLANTS: Nina McDonnell, 1010 Market Street, Suite 1100, St. Louis, Missouri 63101. FOR RESPONDENTS: Dora A. Fichter, Eric Schmitt, P.O. Box 899, Jefferson City, Missouri 65102. Before Sherri B. Sullivan, P.J., James M. Dowd, J., and Robin Ransom, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

Donald Washington appeals the judgment entered upon his convictions following a jury trial in the Circuit Court of the City of St. Louis of one count of second-degree domestic assault and one count of third-degree domestic assault. We affirm.

An extended opinion would have no precedential value. The parties have been furnished with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this order pursuant to Rule 30.25.
